text.tspan: The top unit retreats to its
left and the middle unit
retreats to its rear.
These stands
move left.
This stand retreats
These stands
are detroyed.
Here is a blocked retreat in two stages.
On the left is shown the initial position
and the retreat paths for each retreating
unit.
On the right is the result of a retreat of
4 cm. The rear defeated unit moved to
the side and away from its contacted edge
– creating a space for one stand from the
front unit to move back. In practise, a
retreat of such a large distance would
result in casualties, but we've left all
stands in place to illustrate the process.
